z=z(x,y)
\Phi(x+az,y+bz)=0\quad(a,b\in\mathbb R)
z=z(x,y)
a\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}+b\frac{\partial z}{\partial y}=-1
\Phi
x+az,y+bz
\Phi^\prime
a+b
a+b\neq0\Leftrightarrow a\neq -b
z=z(x,y)
\Phi(x+az(x,y),y+bz(x,y))=0
\frac{\partial \Phi}{\partial z}\neq 0
z=z(x,y)
\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}=\frac{\frac{\partial \Phi}{\partial x}}{\frac{\partial \Phi}{\partial z}}=\frac{1}{a+b},\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}=\frac{\frac{\partial \Phi}{\partial y}}{\frac{\partial \Phi}{\partial z}}=\frac{1}{a+b}
\frac{a+b}{a+b}=1\neq -1
